<NEW>

Quickly they reached another room, this one filled with monitors and
control panels. There was a soldier in the room, he looked to have a
similar dinosaur motif as the rest.

"Where are they?" SABERBACK asked without any introduction. He didn't
really seem to need it as he was obviously talking of the escaped
MAXIMALS.

There was a nod from the other occupant a technician who looked likea
shorter version of TERRORSAUR but also with different colors. "Just a
moment we are bringing it up now."

On the viewscreen was a picture of a large dark chamber. "They just
left this room and are on their way down. It is diffuclt to get a
signal through to get a live feed from there."

SABERBACK nodded, "Yes yes." He said "How long till we get a transmat
link set up?"

"Momentarilly." The technician answered. "We are getting the remote
chamber set up now."

SABERBACK grunted as he crossed his arms over his chest. "We don't
have much time."

The technician nodded, "We have to puch a hole through the
interfearance." He said. "Although it does help that we know the
patturn it is disrupting on."

Behind SABERBACK the SHARKTICON guards were getting a little curoius
as they too looked on at the work being done, watching the technician
work. They were looking between SABERBACK and the technician, for the
moment almost ignoring NIGHTLIGHT.

(TAG)

- Preston
